  _panels:
  - title: skeleton
    description: The dog skeletal system provides structure, support, and protection
      to the body. It is made up of bones such as the skull, spine, ribs, and limbs,
      which help the dog move, maintain balance, and protect vital organs like the
      brain, heart, and lungs. The skeletal system also works together with muscles
      to enable movement and flexibility.
  - title: cute
    description: small dogs are very cute
  - title: organs
    description: The organ system of a dog consists of important internal organs
      such as the heart, lungs, liver, stomach, kidneys, and intestines. These organs
      work together to perform essential functions like breathing, digestion, blood
      circulation, waste removal, and maintaining overall body health. Each organ
      has a specific role that helps the dog survive and function properly.
